### Version

Yosys 0.52+117 (git sha1 bfe05965f, clang++ 14.0.0-1ubuntu1.1 -fsanitize=address -fsanitize=undefined -fPIC -O3 -O1 -fno-omit-frame-pointer -fno-optimize-sibling-calls -fsanitize=address,undefined)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Below is the Verilog file `test.v` that causes the bug, and I have already minimized it.

```verilog
`timescale 1ns/1ps

module top (
    input  wire signed [21:21] in0,
    input        clock_0,
    input        clock_2
);

    wire clock_0;
    wire clock_2;
    reg signed [28:26] reg_10;

    always @(posedge clock_0 or posedge clock_2) begin
        $display("always block is triggered......");

        if (clock_2) begin
            $display("now in clock_2 == true branch");
        end else begin
            $display("now in clock_2 == false branch");

            if (in0) begin
                reg_10[28:26] <= 2;
            end else begin
                reg_10[28:27] <= 1;
            end
        end
    end

endmodule
```

Run the following commands to optimize it:

```
read_verilog test.v
opt
proc
write_verilog opt.v
```

Yosys generates the corresponding optimized file `opt.v`:

```verilog
/* Generated by Yosys 0.52+117 (git sha1 bfe05965f, clang++ 14.0.0-1ubuntu1.1 -fsanitize=address -fsanitize=undefined -fPIC -O3 -O1 -fno-omit-frame-pointer -fno-optimize-sibling-calls -fsanitize=address,undefined) */

(* cells_not_processed =  1  *)
(* src = "test.v:3.1-29.10" *)
module top(in0, clock_0, clock_2);
  (* src = "test.v:13.5-27.8" *)
  wire [2:0] _00_;
  wire _01_;
  wire [2:0] _02_;
  (* src = "test.v:14.9-14.53" *)
  wire _03_;
  (* src = "test.v:17.13-17.55" *)
  wire _04_;
  (* src = "test.v:19.13-19.56" *)
  wire _05_;
  wire _06_;
  wire _07_;
  (* src = "test.v:5.18-5.25" *)
  input clock_0;
  wire clock_0;
  (* src = "test.v:6.18-6.25" *)
  input clock_2;
  wire clock_2;
  (* src = "test.v:4.32-4.35" *)
  input in0;
  wire in0;
  (* src = "test.v:11.24-11.30" *)
  reg [28:26] reg_10;
  assign _02_ = _01_ ? reg_10 : { 2'h1, _06_ };
  (* src = "test.v:13.5-27.8" *)
  always @(posedge clock_0)
    reg_10 <= _02_;
  assign _06_ = _07_ ? (* full_case = 32'd1 *) (* src = "test.v:21.17-21.20|test.v:21.13-25.16" *) 1'h0 : reg_10[26];
  always @(posedge clock_0 or posedge clock_2) begin
    if (1'h1) begin
      $write("always block is triggered......\n");
    end
    if (1'h0) begin
      $write("now in clock_2 == true branch\n");
    end
    if (1'h1) begin
      $write("now in clock_2 == false branch\n");
    end
  end
  assign _03_ = 1'h1;
  assign _00_[2:1] = 2'h1;
  assign _07_ = in0;
  assign _00_[0] = _06_;
  assign _04_ = 1'h0;
  assign _05_ = 1'h1;
  assign _01_ = clock_2;
endmodule
```

Looking at the following lines in `opt.v`:

```verilog
  always @(posedge clock_0 or posedge clock_2) begin
    if (1'h1) begin
      $write("always block is triggered......\n");
    end
    if (1'h0) begin
      $write("now in clock_2 == true branch\n");
    end
    if (1'h1) begin
      $write("now in clock_2 == false branch\n");
    end
  end
```

We can see that in the original unoptimized code, the following conditional branches should be triggered, but in the optimized code, they are hardcoded and will never be triggered:

```verilog
        if (clock_2) begin
            $display("now in clock_2 == true branch");
```

In fact, this branch should be triggered when `clock_2` has a rising edge.

By the way, during local debugging I found that if the following lines are removed from the original (unoptimized) code, the optimized code no longer exhibits this error. Hope this helps with debugging the issue:

```verilog
            if (in0) begin
                reg_10[28:26] <= 2;
            end else begin
                reg_10[28:27] <= 1;
            end
```


### Expected Behavior

When there is a rising edge on `clock_2`, the `always @(posedge clock_0 or posedge clock_2)` block should be triggered. Inside this block, the condition `if (clock_2)` should evaluate to `true`, and the message `"now in clock_2 == true branch"` should be printed via `$display`.


### Actual Behavior

In the optimized output (`opt.v`), Yosys has replaced `if (clock_2)` with `if (1'h0)`, making the `"now in clock_2 == true branch"` branch unreachable. As a result, even when `clock_2` has a rising edge, this message is never printed. This breaks the functional behavior of the original design.

